olive oil
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet chicken breast
2 eggs
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 tsp sesame oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet ginger paste
1 tsp soy sauce
1 packet mayonnaise
1 bag coriander
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Drain the sweetcorn. Roughly chop baby spinach leaves.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• In the last 2 minutes of cook time, add sweetcorn and ginger paste and cook, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add the soy sauce, sesame oil, Korean stir-fry sauce and a splash of water, and cook until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

• Wash and dry the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Crack the eggs into the pan and cook until egg whites are firm and yolks are cooked to your liking, 4-5 minutes.
• Meanwhile, combine slaw mix and baby spinach in a medium bowl, along with mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar.

TIP: Cooking the eggs for 4-5 minutes will give a soft yolk. Cook for 6-7 minutes to get a hard yolk.

• Divide creamy slaw between bowls. Top with Korean chicken, corn and a fried egg.
• Tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!